  <name>Tilepaint</name>

  <!-- Translators: the brief summary of the application as it appears in a software center. -->
  <summary>Master the art of deduction in this modern logic puzzle game</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Tilepaint (also known as Crazy Pavement) is a logic puzzle where the goal is to paint cells in a grid divided into regions (tiles). The puzzle is solved when all regions are correctly set to either painted or unpainted, following two core rules:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Each region must be either entirely painted or entirely unpainted.</li>
      <li>The clue numbers at the top and left of the grid indicate exactly how many cells in each column and row must be painted.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Rebuilt for the modern GNOME desktop, Tilepaint features a beautiful, adaptive user interface
      using GTK4 and Libadwaita. It offers a relaxing yet challenging experience with multiple board sizes,
      keyboard navigation, and helper tools to guide your way.
    </p>
  </description>
