  <releases>
    <release version="1.0.1" date="2026-02-08" type="stable">
      <description>
        <p>Tilepaint 1.0.1 is a patch release improving the victory logic.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>**Relaxed Victory Condition**: The game now accepts any board state that visually matches the row and column clues, resolving cases where valid solutions were rejected.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.0.0" date="2026-02-08" type="stable">
      <description>
        <p>Tilepaint 1.0.0 is a major release, reimagining the logic puzzle for the modern GNOME ecosystem.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>**Guaranteed Unique Solutions**: Every generated puzzle is now verified to have exactly one solution.</li>
          <li>**Anti-Peeking Features**: The pause overlay now hides clue numbers, and the board rendering is perfectly consistent to prevent solution leaks.</li>
          <li>**Tile-based Logic**: New game mechanics focusing on region-based painting and clue totals.</li>
          <li>**Modern Foundation**: Complete rewrite using GTK4 and Libadwaita for a fluid, adaptive UI.</li>
          <li>**System Color Integration**: Clue numbers and board themes adapt to your system's light/dark mode.</li>
          <li>**Enhanced Accessibility**: Full keyboard navigation support (WASD, HJKL, or Arrow keys).</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>
